{"wiki_catalogs":[{"id":"c37b7950-c1af-4c4d-a14d-d51018df225f","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"Project Overview","description":"project-overview","prompt":"Create comprehensive content for this portfolio website project overview. Explain the purpose of this static portfolio website, its target audience, and key features including responsive design, theme switching, and multi-page navigation. Document the project's architecture as a traditional multi-page static website using vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript without external dependencies. Include both conceptual overviews for beginners understanding static websites and technical details for experienced developers. Use terminology consistent with the codebase such as 'static website', 'responsive design', and 'theme management'. Provide practical examples demonstrating the portfolio structure and common use cases like showcasing work, displaying projects, and contact form functionality.","progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/index.html,portfolio/sitemap.xml","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.4098173+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:02.9247937+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"39684451-8c59-4df7-b942-248350fda4c4","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"Getting Started","description":"getting-started","prompt":"Create comprehensive getting started documentation for this portfolio website. Explain prerequisites including basic knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Document local development setup using the provided PowerShell server script (server.ps1) for running the site locally. Include step-by-step installation instructions, basic usage examples for navigating the portfolio pages, and guidance on how to view the website in different browsers. Address file organization basics and explain how the static website structure works. Make content accessible to beginners while providing sufficient technical depth for experienced developers setting up their development environment.","order":1,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/server.ps1,portfolio/index.html","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.410479+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:09.0916677+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"48901c51-25cc-44a5-88cc-bbb4960ae1e1","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"File Structure \u0026 Organization","description":"file-structure","prompt":"Create detailed documentation for the portfolio website's file structure and organization. Explain the directory layout including the separation of concerns with CSS files organized by purpose (style.css for base styles, responsive.css for mobile-first breakpoints, theme.css for theme variables). Document the JavaScript organization with centralized theme management in theme.js. Detail file naming conventions, asset organization patterns, and how HTML pages reference shared CSS and JS files. Include explanations of the modular CSS architecture and how components relate to each other. Provide practical examples showing how to add new styles or modify existing functionality while maintaining the established organizational patterns.","order":2,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/css/style.css,portfolio/css/responsive.css,portfolio/css/theme.css,portfolio/js/theme.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.410479+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:05.175204+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"a1e1bca4-5747-4cac-ade8-fd9d486c02cd","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"Core Pages Documentation","description":"core-pages","prompt":"Create comprehensive documentation for all core pages of the portfolio website. Document each page's purpose, structure, and key features: index.html (home page with hero section and navigation), about.html (personal information and skills showcase), projects.html (portfolio project display), and contact.html (contact form implementation). Explain the semantic HTML structure used across pages, navigation consistency, and how each page integrates with the shared styling system. Include details about responsive behavior, accessibility considerations, and customization options for each page. Provide examples of how to modify content, add new sections, and maintain consistency across pages.","order":3,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/index.html,portfolio/about.html,portfolio/projects.html,portfolio/contact.html","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.4143055+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:38.0096352+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"e27b2411-5e55-4e32-b76d-923790ac303e","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"Styling System \u0026 Theme Management","description":"styling-system","prompt":"Create detailed documentation for the portfolio website's styling system and theme management. Explain the modular CSS architecture with base styles in style.css, responsive breakpoints in responsive.css, and theme variables in theme.css. Document the CSS custom properties implementation for theming, including color schemes, typography, and layout variables. Detail the responsive design strategy using mobile-first approach and media queries. Explain the JavaScript theme switching functionality in theme.js, including how themes persist across sessions and how to add new color schemes. Include practical examples of customizing colors, fonts, and layout while maintaining responsive behavior. Address cross-browser compatibility and performance optimization techniques used in the styling system.","order":4,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/css/style.css,portfolio/css/responsive.css,portfolio/css/theme.css,portfolio/js/theme.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.4143055+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:55.9477568+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"6022173d-aed6-43cb-b5da-c96e63debe63","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"Development Tools \u0026 Configuration","description":"development-tools","prompt":"Create comprehensive documentation for development tools and configuration files. Document the PowerShell server script (server.ps1) for local development, including how to run it, port configuration, and troubleshooting common issues. Explain the sitemap.xml configuration for SEO optimization, including how to update it when adding new pages or modifying URLs. Include guidance on browser developer tools usage for debugging the portfolio website, performance monitoring, and testing responsive design across different screen sizes. Address best practices for version control, file organization during development, and deployment preparation. Provide examples of common development workflows and maintenance tasks.","order":5,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"portfolio/server.ps1,portfolio/sitemap.xml","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:13:30.4155076+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:53.7089905+05:30","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"}],"wiki_items":[{"catalog_id":"c37b7950-c1af-4c4d-a14d-d51018df225f","title":"Project Overview","description":"project-overview","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"cd692360-312a-4815-b7a7-839267956753","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:02.9192543+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:02.9247937+05:30"},{"catalog_id":"48901c51-25cc-44a5-88cc-bbb4960ae1e1","title":"File Structure \u0026 Organization","description":"file-structure","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"c39f1f7d-de8b-47a9-81ae-159821be67f8","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:05.1686201+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:05.175204+05:30"},{"catalog_id":"39684451-8c59-4df7-b942-248350fda4c4","title":"Getting Started","description":"getting-started","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"9564d0b5-dcd0-4b39-94f4-da29353a0ecc","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:09.0874741+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:09.0916677+05:30"},{"catalog_id":"a1e1bca4-5747-4cac-ade8-fd9d486c02cd","title":"Core Pages Documentation","description":"core-pages","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"cecd5f7e-8b20-481a-9fb7-9840d79dbaf1","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:38.0036879+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:38.0103526+05:30"},{"catalog_id":"6022173d-aed6-43cb-b5da-c96e63debe63","title":"Development Tools \u0026 Configuration","description":"development-tools","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"bf65eedd-a767-4e8f-a692-bbd186185b56","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:53.7039448+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:53.7096611+05:30"},{"catalog_id":"e27b2411-5e55-4e32-b76d-923790ac303e","title":"Styling System \u0026 Theme Management","description":"styling-system","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","reference_count":0,"id":"9217b294-3229-4fd7-959e-4858ab6d37ff","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:14:55.9433153+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:55.9477568+05:30"}],"wiki_overview":{"content":"\u003c/think\u003e\n\n\u003cblog\u003e\n\n# Portfolio Website Project Analysis\n\n## 1. Project Introduction\n\n### Purpose Statement\nThis is a personal portfolio website project designed to showcase professional work, skills, and contact information through a modern, responsive web interface. The project follows a traditional static website architecture with separate HTML pages for different sections of the portfolio.\n\n### Core Goals and Objectives\n- Present professional portfolio content in an organized, navigable format\n- Provide responsive design that works across various devices and screen sizes\n- Implement theme switching functionality for user preference customization\n- Maintain clean separation of concerns between structure (HTML), styling (CSS), and behavior (JavaScript)\n\n### Target Audience\n- Potential employers and clients reviewing professional work\n- Professional network connections seeking contact information\n- Visitors interested in the developer's background and capabilities\n\n## 2. Technical Architecture\n\nThe project follows a classic multi-page static website architecture with clear separation of concerns:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[Portfolio Website] --\u003e B[HTML Structure Layer]\n    A --\u003e C[Styling Layer]\n    A --\u003e D[Behavior Layer]\n    \n    B --\u003e E[index.html - Home Page]\n    B --\u003e F[about.html - About Section]\n    B --\u003e G[projects.html - Projects Showcase]\n    B --\u003e H[contact.html - Contact Form]\n    \n    C --\u003e I[style.css - Base Styles]\n    C --\u003e J[responsive.css - Mobile Optimization]\n    C --\u003e K[theme.css - Theme Variables]\n    \n    D --\u003e L[theme.js - Theme Management]\n    \n    M[server.ps1 - Development Server] --\u003e A\n    N[sitemap.xml - SEO \u0026 Navigation] --\u003e A\n```\n\n### Component Breakdown\n- **HTML Pages**: Individual page files for each section (home, about, projects, contact)\n- **CSS Architecture**: Modular stylesheet organization with base styles, responsive rules, and theme variables\n- **JavaScript Functionality**: Single JavaScript file handling theme switching and interactive features\n- **Development Tools**: PowerShell script for local development server setup\n\n### Design Patterns\n- **Multi-page Application Pattern**: Traditional navigation between separate HTML files\n- **Separation of Concerns**: Clear division between structure, presentation, and behavior\n- **Mobile-First Responsive Design**: CSS media queries for cross-device compatibility\n- **Theme System**: CSS custom properties for dynamic styling changes\n\n## 3. Key Implementation\n\n### Main Entry Points\n- **index.html** - Primary landing page serving as the main entry point\n- **server.ps1** - Development server configuration for local testing\n\n### Core Modules\n- **HTML Structure** (`*.html` files) - Semantic markup for each portfolio section\n- **CSS Architecture** (`css/` directory) - Organized stylesheet system with modular components\n- **Theme Management** (`js/theme.js`) - JavaScript logic for theme switching functionality\n\n### Configuration Approach\n- **Static Site Configuration**: No build tools or complex configuration management\n- **File-based Routing**: Direct URL mapping to HTML files\n- **Asset Organization**: Logical grouping of related files by type and purpose\n\n### External Dependencies\n- **No Framework Dependencies**: Pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript implementation\n- **Browser Compatibility**: Standard web technologies ensuring broad browser support\n- **Development Tools**: PowerShell for local development server setup\n\n### Integration Points\n- **SEO Integration**: `sitemap.xml` for search engine optimization\n- **Responsive Images**: Optimized asset loading for different screen sizes\n- **Cross-browser Styling**: CSS fallbacks and vendor prefixes for compatibility\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n    A[User Browser] --\u003e B[HTML Pages]\n    B --\u003e C[CSS Stylesheets]\n    B --\u003e D[JavaScript Logic]\n    C --\u003e E[Theme System]\n    D --\u003e E\n    E --\u003e F[Dynamic Styling]\n```\n\n## 4. Key Features\n\n### Functionality Overview\n- **Multi-section Portfolio**: Dedicated pages for different content types\n- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with adaptive layouts\n- **Theme Switching**: Dynamic light/dark mode toggle functionality\n- **Navigation System**: Consistent menu structure across all pages\n- **Contact Integration**: Form handling and contact information display\n\n### Implementation Highlights\n- **Modular CSS Architecture** (`css/style.css`, `css/responsive.css`, `css/theme.css`)\n- **Centralized Theme Management** (`js/theme.js`)\n- **Semantic HTML Structure** (individual page files)\n- **Performance Optimization** (minimal dependencies, optimized assets)\n\n### Feature Architecture\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --\u003e DefaultTheme\n    DefaultTheme --\u003e DarkTheme: Theme Toggle\n    DarkTheme --\u003e DefaultTheme: Theme Toggle\n    \n    [*] --\u003e HomePage\n    HomePage --\u003e AboutPage: Navigation\n    HomePage --\u003e ProjectsPage: Navigation\n    HomePage --\u003e ContactPage: Navigation\n    \n    AboutPage --\u003e HomePage: Back Navigation\n    ProjectsPage --\u003e HomePage: Back Navigation\n    ContactPage --\u003e HomePage: Back Navigation\n```\n\n### Responsive Design Strategy\n- **Mobile-First Approach**: Base styles optimized for smaller screens\n- **Breakpoint System**: Strategic media queries for tablet and desktop views\n- **Flexible Layouts**: CSS Grid and Flexbox for adaptive component positioning\n- **Touch-Friendly Interface**: Optimized interaction elements for mobile devices\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [index.html](portfolio/index.html)\n- [about.html](portfolio/about.html)\n- [projects.html](portfolio/projects.html)\n- [contact.html](portfolio/contact.html)\n- [style.css](portfolio/css/style.css)\n- [responsive.css](portfolio/css/responsive.css)\n- [theme.css](portfolio/css/theme.css)\n- [theme.js](portfolio/js/theme.js)\n- [server.ps1](portfolio/server.ps1)\n- [sitemap.xml](portfolio/sitemap.xml)\n\n\u003c/blog\u003e","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:12:30.4856928+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:12:30.4856928+05:30","id":"0a220fa2-0599-4b85-ae74-6b412be0d3d7","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570"},"wiki_readme":{"content":"No readme file","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:11:33.1431806+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:11:33.1431806+05:30","id":"c29a4335-863f-4c32-b3d9-4b19ece5357c","repo_id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570"},"wiki_repo":{"id":"238a4d4f-a01e-442a-aa79-5920a3e5a570","name":"architecture","progress_status":"completed","wiki_present_status":"COMPLETED","optimized_catalog":"\".\\n└── portfolio\\\\\\n    ├── css\\\\\\n    │   ├── responsive.css\\n    │   ├── style.css\\n    │   └── theme.css\\n    ├── js\\\\\\n    │   └── theme.js\\n    ├── about.html\\n    ├── contact.html\\n    ├── index.html\\n    ├── projects.html\\n    ├── server.ps1\\n    └── sitemap.xml\\n\"","current_document_structure":"WikiEncrypted:","catalogue_think_content":"WikiEncrypted:","recovery_checkpoint":"wiki_generation_completed","last_commit_id":"0000000000000000000000000000000000000000","last_commit_update":"2026-07-16T22:14:55.953977+05:30","gmt_create":"2026-07-16T22:11:32.8774859+05:30","gmt_modified":"2026-07-16T22:14:55.953977+05:30","extend_info":"{\"language\":\"en\",\"active\":true,\"branch\":\"Q0DeR-MaG1C-BrAnCh-Fo2-NoN-GiT-Or-No-C0MmIt\",\"shareStatus\":\"\",\"server_error_code\":\"\",\"cosy_version\":\"\"}"}}